tip.text: After trying most tapas places in London by now, this place is the best. All seafood is good, the artichoke was excellent
Great service, Excellent Irish breakfast and I also loved the kiwi smoothy.

Portions are very generous, seafood chowder was good as was the mussels and clams. Partner had the smoked haddock which she loved. Topped off with the rhubarb desert which was a the perfect way to end
Good coffee, truffle pasta was great. Clean bathrooms
Lobster tacos were amazing, as was the surf and turf. Guacamole was good too.
Not really a gastropub, nice little restaurant, serves great brunch
